replies.bodyText: Do we need Document to extend from HashMap, or is it sufficient that it have a map-like API?
replies.author: JonathanGiles

replies.bodyText: @JonathanGiles Strictly speaking no. I think that was done for implementation convenience. It also means that SearchDocument (formerly Document) implements Map. The only scenario I can imagine where that's necessary is interop with other JVM languages.
replies.author: brjohnstmsft

timeline.bodyText: I had to add SearchError to the Swagger for the sake of JS/TS, but it's my understanding that this is a subset of a well-defined error contract for Microsoft REST APIs. Do we actually need to expose this, or is there some Azure Core type for error payloads that overlaps SearchError?
